



Dr Sir
Mount Vernon 30th April 1775



I shall be much obliged to you for the interest due on your Bond in Novr last, to wit 401It is not in my power to attend the meeting of Merchants in Williamsburg this Spring, but Colo. Fielding Lewis will do me the favour to negotiate my business this Court.2 I am with respectful compliments to Mrs Lewis & your Family3& with very great esteem Dr Sir, Your most Obt Servt

G: Washington

